The EU conflict analysis, early warning and policy options to intervene in conflict and crisis situations is strengthened through the implementation period.1. Increased understanding on the part of the EU and other target groups of conflict risks and dynamics, including gender dynamics, as well as entry points and opportunities for early action.2. The EU is better equipped and uses fieldcentred analysis to address the main drivers of violent conflicts, produces more effective and timely responses, and more conflict sensitive policies and programmes for the prevention, mitigation and resolution of violent conflict.3. The EU uses early warning information and fieldbased conflict analysis and advice to develop effective preventive responses.4. Increased understanding by the EU of the usefulness of exchanging conflict analysis and jointly discussing policy strategies, particularly with local and international actors, including civil society.

According to the latest information received from the Commander of Border Troops of Tajikistan there are more than 12000 terrorists representing more than 18 different terrorist groups deployed in the border with Tajikistan on the Afghan side. The number of border outposts in the border line with Afghanistan have increased by 70 and the number of detachments will be increased by 50. The President of Tajikistan has recently ordered to increase the number of Tajikistans border troops by 10000 at the border line with Afghanistan. There is a need to construct at least 45 additional training centres several hospitals across the border with Afghanistan containers for soldiers in the outposts as well as to provide them with additional equipment for patrolling and serving at the border line with Afghanistan. This also requires to conduct additional and more training for newcomers. Unfortunately the current project with its limited budget and resources cannot respond to all these challenges however it is responding to a significant degree to those challenges that are defined in the Description of Action.

Activities implemented to achieve the purpose aimed at ensuring valuable communication about the Project to national partners international development community civil society academia multipliers media and other influencers professional society. The main interventions targeted availing adequate information to external stakeholders and the Basotho public about the activities and results of the Project. Similarly they  ensure a wide engagement of key targeted stakeholders and presented targeted consistent messages of the Project for specific groups of the audience.To ensure a harmonious and wellcoordinated approach to communications and visibility among the different components of the Action a sustained communication and visibility campaign reached an estimated 45 of Basotho. This was derived from television viewership newspaper circulation social media content and comments on content related to the high profile cases. Some of the key activities undertaken to reach this target include a the conceptualization design development and approval by Judiciary the public information and communication campaign activities b sustained media articles radio and TV programmes as well as social media activities on the high profile cases. This was complimented by routine advertisement media engagement on the trial process Judges and Magistrates Colloquium public debates on TV call in radio talk shows and sustained social media campaigns for the Strategic Plan development and launch end of project evaluation validation and media articles.The strategic media engagement continued in the Phase II of the Project by a Communicating Project goals objectives outputs and results to the media for purposes of proposes platforms for media involvement programme implementation and encourage synergies b generating a common understanding on the medias role in framing and expanding positive discussion and debate of issues related to implementation of Project  c proposing mechanisms and strategies to engage the media owners content creators and critical corporations that produce media for purposes of promoting balanced reporting content creation and distribution on the Project.The communication and visibilities activities were also sustained through conceptualization design generation and development of multimedia content including media releases stories videos posters and infographics. Key content generated and produced as posters pullup banners wall banners radio messages and newspaper articles stationary and digital messages. The capacity of the Judiciarys public relations media and communication unit to inform the public on the Project was enhanced through procurement of multimedia tools training of key personnel on media engagement and content creation and establishment of a documentation centre with current content.Through the implementation of the Communication and Visibilities Plan the first Judiciary dedicated website was developed hosted and launched httpsjud.gov.ls . This ensured Judgements and court processes were easily accessible as they were uploaded on the website. The Website shall in the future publish judgments from the subordinate courts. Courtrelated information and procedures was made accessible and available to the public for scrutiny.
